Description:
A Family Delight In The Perfect Locale
Solidly built and flaunting a versatile floor plan with easy enhancement potential, this two storey three bedroom plus study, two bathroom home will delight market entrants and growing families. This well loved residence comprises a broad living and dining room with an enclosed retro bar, split system and soaring ceilings which enhance the space. Situated to the rear of the home is an open plan kitchen and family room showcasing updated stainless steel appliances including dishwasher plus generous bench space and cabinetry. Glass sliders reveal a spacious paved alfresco, while enveloping the home is an easy care garden including a mature lemon tree and garden shed. The master bedroom resides on the ground floor enjoying original ensuite and dual floor to ceiling BIR's while atop the timber staircase is two additional bedrooms serviced by a central bathroom and private W/C. Further highlights include double carport, ducted heating, hardwood floors throughout and a second toilet via the spacious laundry. Bus service, Keilor Village, excellent schools including Overnewton College and St Augustines are all mere minutes away as is Brimbank Park, Watergardens shopping centre, train station and freeway access.
Insights: 9 Tarwin Court, Keilor VIC 3036 was last sold in 2017 and 27 other 3 bedroom house in Keilor have recently been sold.

Under Offer

Description:
Spacious Villa In A Prized Village Locale
Enjoy a charmed lifestyle with this exceptionally spacious three bedroom, two bathroom villa offering a convenient, safe environment. Situated opposite Keilor Recreation Reserve, in a boutique block of three, the immaculately presented property has been in the same family since it was first built. Beyond its Federation inspired facade lies an expansive open plan living space featuring box bay window, high ceilings and new carpet. An adjoining dining area sits next to a light filled kitchen as well as an open study/sitting zone enjoying sliding door access to a delightful all season courtyard bathed in northerly light. Fully equipped with quality cooking appliances, dishwasher and abundant storage, the kitchen also enjoys central aspect and garden views. Freshly painted, it features three bedrooms, including main with walk-in-robe and ensuite. Highlights comprise BIR'S, pristine bathroom, ducted heating, storage and automated double garage, with direct home entry via laundry, plus off street parking. Steps from Keilor Village cafes, shops, buses and schools, it offers superb lifestyle choices.

Description:
Outstanding Potential In Keilors Premier Pocket
Favoured by frontage in a picturesque street, moments to friendly Keilor Village, this inviting three bedroom home has much to offer buyers ready to show their style with savvy enhancements or seeking to try something new (subject to relevant approvals). Introduced by a wraparound verandah and exhibiting polished floorboards and a practical layout, the home presents a central kitchen with a gas stove and breakfast bar, open living and dining domains and a covered entertainer's deck overlooking a rear garden with additional barbecue area. The three double bedrooms include built-in robes and all are serviced by a central bathroom hosting a bath, two showers, vanity and toilet. The laundry leads to a convenient separate toilet, heating and air conditioning add comfort, and there are sheds for additional storage. Transport, Keilor Primary School and reserves are just a short stroll, the many village shops and cafes within an easy walk, and freeway access only a quick drive away.

The exterior features a barbeque area and a separate relaxation space complemented by large cantilevered umbrella, outdoor sound system and low-maintenance garden. Light-filled interiors comprise large open plan living, sociable dining area and a large entertainer's kitchen all framed by polished timber floors. This home features four bedrooms, two offer built-in-robes, family bathroom, guest powder room, efficient heating and cooling, excellent storage, over-sized double garage with remote-control access and rear doorway. Hermes Court is within minutes of playgrounds/fitness stations, Keilor Village cafes and shops, scenic walking trails, Green Gully Reserve, well regarded schools and well established transport links.

Description:
Reach For The Sky!
In Room Auction Wednesday 29th March 2017, 7:00pm - Monmia Primary School, Copernicus Way, Keilor Downs VIC 3038
Set high on the hill in the heart of Keilor Village sits this solid family home that sets the absolute standard for family living. As you enter the home you will find a large study, formal dining room and a formal lounge room complete with timber floorboards and cathedral ceilings. Add to this a well-appointed kitchen with quality appliances. The home's second-level interior comprises four spacious bedrooms with built in robes and a central family bathroom. The master complete with an en-suite and walk in robe; from your master bedroom you can step onto your very own balcony to enjoy the breathtaking panoramic views. Lets not forget the large in-ground swimming pool, perfect for the warmer months! Other features include an over-sized double garage, ducted heating and evaporate cooling plus a private backyard garden. Walking distance to village shops/cafes and historic Keilor Hotel, local schools, Brimbank Park and Maribyrnong River trails, public transport and easy freeway access. Just 15 minutes from Melbourne, this is an outstanding home rarely seen in such a fabulous location!

Description:
Family Favourite Close To Keilor Village
Entertaining is easy with this deceptively spacious three bedroom, two bathroom two-storey brick family residence delivering harmonious living, dining spaces matched with a fully enclosed spa room. Step inside where a wide central entry space introduces a light filled lounge, formal dining room, bright open study area and large family zone featuring a Norseman wood heater perfect for the cooler seasons and relaxing times with family and friends. Enjoying a garden outlook, and direct access to the spa room, is an open plan kitchen, meals zone displaying gas stove, dishwasher and refurbished cabinetry, including generous pantry. Upstairs find three double bedrooms, two boast built-in-robes and elevated views. They share a beautifully renovated bathroom featuring double shower, his/hers stone-top vanities, luxury bath and toilet. Additional highlights include ducted heating, evaporative cooling, downstairs laundry/second bathroom, polished floorboards, paved outdoor zones, shed, double carport and land approximately 542m2. Within moments from Keilor Village cafes, shops, top schools, Green Gully Reserve, sports clubs and freeways.

Description:
Delight In The Potential, Revel In The Locale
Presenting outstanding living on a grand scale, this imposing, double storey four bedroom, three bathroom residence, will prove to be the forever home of your growing family. The well proportioned and considered floor plan facilitates easy enhancing courtesy of your own personal styling. Comprising a sizeable rumpus, formal lounge, separate formal dining room, combined living, dining and kitchen featuring gas cooking and plenty of bench/cabinet space, plus a long covered alfresco area and grassy yard outdoor enjoyment is assured. Nestled at the top of the staircase is the accommodation, a generous master with ensuite and WIR and three bedrooms, (two with balcony access), plus study/fifth bedroom, all maintaining handy access to the oversized main bathroom. Modern comforts include double remote garage with storage space, ducted heating, ducted vacuum, alarm, under stair storage and garden shed. Enhancing the homes unique appeal is the ultra-convenient locale, walking distance to St Augustine's Primary School, Overnewton College, parks and transport, and only minutes to Taylors Lakes and Watergardens Shopping Centres, train station and easy access to Calder freeway.

Description:
Family Living In Tranquil Surrounds
Fronting Stuart Court on a generous corner allotment, is this tranquilly set, pristinely presented three bedroom home. A central entry progresses to spacious living areas on the left and generous accommodation of three bedrooms (two with BIRs) on the right. Large, flowing lounge and dining areas extend to a serene deck overlooking an Asian inspired garden. The updated light filled kitchen with an abundance of storage and features stainless steel cooking appliances, dishwasher and accesses a fabulous pergola covered alfresco area. There's also a separate study/studio, laundry, neat bathroom, good storage, solar panels, cubby house, evaporative and split system cooling plus ducted heating and a charming wood heater. A remote roller door ensures secure parking for four vehicles inclusive of a double carport plus a fifth in the driveway. Summarised, it's an ideal family home in an equally suitable neighbourhood close to Keilor Village, parkland, public transport, schools and Calder Freeway.
